---
import BaseLayout from "@layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
	title="Publishing Workflow — phi9.space"
	description="How Obsidian notes become public research and dataset pages on phi9.space."
>
  <article class="publishing-page">
    <p class="publishing-kicker">Publishing</p>
    <h1>How content moves from Obsidian to phi9.space</h1>
    <p class="publishing-intro">
      The Obsidian vault is the source of truth. Public pages are generated from selected notes and validated
      before deployment.
    </p>

    <section>
      <h2>1. Author in the vault</h2>
      <p>Create or edit notes in <code>5 - Full Notes</code> inside the vault path.</p>
      <p>
        Set frontmatter based on intent:
        <code>type: note</code> for research,
        <code>type: dataset</code> for dataset pages.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>2. Choose what becomes public</h2>
      <p>
        A note is private by default. Set <code>publish: true</code> only when the note is ready for public
        listing and linking.
      </p>
      <p>
        Recommended editorial workflow is <code>status: draft</code> → <code>review</code> → <code>published</code>.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>3. Run sync + validation</h2>
      <p>Use the website repo commands:</p>
      <pre><code>npm run vault:sync
npm run vault:check
npm run build</code></pre>
      <p>
        Sync exports publishable markdown into <code>src/content/vault</code>, copies referenced media into
        <code>public/vault-media</code>, and writes the public note manifest used by navigation, backlinks, and graph.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>4. Verify section behavior</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Research</strong>: note pages and indexes from <code>type: note</code>.</li>
        <li><strong>Datasets</strong>: card index and detail pages from <code>type: dataset</code>.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .publishing-page {
    max-width: 76ch;
    display: grid;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .publishing-kicker {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 0.74rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.13em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  .publishing-intro {
    margin-top: 0.2rem;
    color: var(--color-muted);
  }

  .publishing-page section {
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.35rem;
  }

  .publishing-page ul {
    margin: 0;
  }

  .publishing-page p {
    margin: 0;
  }
</style>
